<br>
Thats a mighty bold statement, I am glad to see that you speak for the core of FS.  You can blame me for people leaving, and yes a few left because of decisions that were made by leadership.  <br>
<br>
The rest that have moved on are leaving for the desire of higher end content.  This has been a long time coming, and to be honest, im surprised it didnt happen sooner.  everyone makes mistakes, and perhaps if the anon poster had the balls to reveal his own name we could all have a better understanding of his frustration.  <br>
<br>
Whatever anyones opinion of me may be, and whatever drama you may wish to start yet again dragging my name in to your issues, go for it.  I am one person.  I can take accountability for me, and me only.  I do not believe that I have treated anyone unfairly.  <br>
<br>
Bottom line was, FS degenerated from having 70 people online at any given time to having 50 then 40 then 30.  We can't raid jack with those numbers.  If you wish to blame me entirely for the fall of FS, thats fabulous. <br>
<br>
To be honest?   I was looking for an out personally.  Scraping the bottom of the barrel for someone to lead this guild came up with me.  Abandonded by the 2 previous guild leaders and not wanting to see FS fail, I tried my best.<br>
<br>
It's really difficult to lead people when a great majority of the guild wants to be constructive and the rest want to be destructive. I am sure this flame will also degenerate in to a post about how I loot whored everything from FS and how FS was there for nothing but my amusement.  That's fine.<br>
<br>
Unless you have lead a guild this size, you can't really know what it's like to log in and be inundated with complaints for 6 hours straight.  Not to mention the emais at work, the phone calls to members to better understand their drama and the attempts to resolve customer service issues to keep your guild afloat.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
 Hayleys attempt to just make the truth go away again pretty much guaranteed that wouldnt happen.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Your issue was with me, not the people that you attempted to drag in to your flame. <br>
<br>
I don't mind the truth, but stick to your main issue, don't try to drag innocent people in to your attempt to thrash me. I will admit that I failed FS, and for that I am truly sorry. <br>
<br>
People don't like me for whatever reason, and thats ok too. Different people have different approaches to getting the same things done. I took an aggressive approach to leading FS rather than a meek one. Perhaps this meant pissing a few people off, but I didn't know any other way to bring this guild in to the higher end game. I made some mistakes, burned some bridges, and yes, the good with the bad gained some respect. <br>
<br>
I don't care what people think of me, and I don't care that I have to shoulder the blame for several members leaving. It's only natural to have to blame and point fingers when something happens we have no control over. <br>
<br>
Several people were unhappy with the lack of FS progression. Heck even I was unhappy with our progression. I did the best I could with these people, and I was honest with them. The people that stuck by this guild, Treehugga, Ninidir, Seule, those of you looking for higher end content, I consider you all the best type of people. I understand your desires to move in to pop, and respect your decision. <br>
<br>
Rather than try to burn more bridges and hold people back, I choose instead to support my friends and guild mates and encourage them to pursue the content that makes them happy. Content I lack the knowledge, and ability to raid. I won't deny that. <br>
<br>
To be honest, I breathe a sigh of relief knowing that I am going to be relieved of some of that stress.  Maybe I can find some enjoyment in that game rather than dread loggin in to hear complaint after complaint. I used to be on leave from my job, and used to have the time to deal with crap like this.  I had to return to work for several reasons.  I just thank god that my employer still held my job after being fine 14 months.<br>
<br>
But alas, I have found sunshine, money, friends and wow...I have a family.  Thank you, for giving me the out I needed.  I really do still wish I could play EQ 15hours per day, and I really do wish I could wade through shit and drama with the fabulous fine people of Saryrn.<br>
<br>
Rather than see any good in the things that I attempted to do for FS, its all bad.  I expect that everyone will have something to say on the matter.  Come on, Lemme have it!<br>
