<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> Do you really attribute the timing between Aono's departure and the guild's decline to pure coincidence? I assure you, it isn't.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
no I attribute it to realizing I had sat on my ass for 14 months in front of this computer, doing nothing but playing this game.  I had no choice but to return to my job, and when I did it helped decline.  I strongly feel that if I hadnt had to return to work, I would be sitting on spawns too.  Both Aono and I had IRL throw us a curve ball, and neither one of us could do what we committed to do.  IRL &gt; EQ.<br>
<br>
If I was doing such a suck ass job, Dakston you were more than welcome to step up and try to help.  Besides there is a lot more to be a leader than simply leading raids.  You have to be a social worker, a counslor, a mother, a vending machine and a punching bag.  One person cant do it all.  Every leader of this guild, necole, tab, aono, myself, xedia, detah and every member made those accomplishments.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> That you can't even speak to members of other guilds on your main characters is just one example that attests to this simple fact. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
What the hell are you talking about?  The only time I talked to someone on my alt was Hareq.  And thats because I was checking Dain...for the love of god people quit grabbing at straws here. With the exception of Tose I can't think of one guild leader that refuses to talk to me.<br>
